cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use nox-mem in your research, please cite this software AND the accompanying paper."
title: "nox-mem: pain-weighted hybrid memory for LLM agents"
abstract: >-
  nox-mem is an open-source persistent memory system for autonomous LLM agent
  fleets. It combines BM25 full-text search (FTS5), semantic vector similarity
  (sqlite-vec, 3072-dim Gemini embeddings), and Reciprocal Rank Fusion into a
  hybrid retrieval pipeline. A pain-weighted salience formula (recency × pain ×
  importance) surfaces high-severity memories under retrieval pressure. An
  LLM-powered knowledge graph with temporal decay and cross-agent intelligence
  sharing completes the stack. Fully self-hosted; zero vendor lock-in.
